The '''Player-owned houses glitch''' was a [[glitch]] that occurred on [[9 December]] [[2020]].

After the [[2020 Christmas Event]] update, various [[player-owned house]] furniture had disappeared for many players. This was hotfixed less than an hour after the update.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Sarnie|url=https://twitter.com/JagexSarnie/status/1336645760654381058|date=9 December 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/fA5tt|archivedate=17 December 2020|quote=We found them and they should of all gone back home now.}}

The day after the glitch, Jagex did another update to fix an issue with [[spirit tree]]s that was causing the tree not to be central in their [[superior garden]] when decorated.{{CiteTwitter|author=Old School RuneScape|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/1336989603501387777|date=10 December 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/Gg4Tw|archivedate=17 December 2020|quote=The coldfix will make the Spirit Trees in your PoH stay in the centre of their respective areas when decorated.}}

